The paper focuses on understanding attention in graph neural networks and its ability to generalize to larger, more complex or noisy graphs. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
